# Responsible Use Guidelines

HEICtoJPG is designed to provide fast, reliable, and local image format conversion for personal and professional workflows.

This project is intended to remain free and accessible.

## Intended Uses

Examples of appropriate use include:

- Personal photo conversion
- Educational or classroom use
- Internal engineering workflows
- Lab or research environments
- Personal automation scripts

## Not Intended For

This software is NOT intended to be:

- Resold or repackaged for profit
- Embedded into paid SaaS products
- Used as a commercial backend service
- Monetized without permission

If your use case involves revenue generation or commercial deployment, please obtain a commercial license.

## Security Reminder

Because HEICtoJPG processes image files:

- Do not run untrusted files on sensitive systems
- Keep dependencies updated
- Use sandboxing in enterprise environments

## Philosophy

This project follows a simple philosophy:

Free for learning, building, and sharing.
Not free for resale.

Respecting these guidelines helps keep the tool open and sustainable for everyone.
